The paper proposes a deep learning model for object detection and semantic part localization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The model is based on a graphical model and uses the R-CNN framework, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model and compares it to other state-of-the-art models, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper mentions the annotation of semantic parts, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
